&lt;p&gt;As a Document Controller, you will play a critical role in managing and safeguarding all technical, design, construction, and compliance documentation across a fast-growing hyperscale data center program.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will ensure that every drawing, model, report, specification, contract, and change document is accurate, traceable, and aligned with strict internal, client, and regulatory requirements. You will act as the &lt;strong&gt;gatekeeper of the project’s single source of truth&lt;/strong&gt;, enabling coordination across engineering, construction, commissioning, quality, operations, consultants, and contractors.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This role is essential to maintain transparency, compliance, and governance as we expand our portfolio and scale our project delivery capabilities.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Responsibilities&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Document Management&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Manage the full lifecycle of project documents - creation, revision, approval, distribution, and archiving - across all project stages.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ensure proper version control, document numbering, and traceability for drawings, specifications, contracts, and reports.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintain and enforce document control procedures in line with company and industry standards.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ensure that all documentation complies with internal policies, client requirements, and regulatory frameworks.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;System Administration &amp;amp; Tools&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Manage the document management platform (e.g., ACC, SharePoint, or similar) and ensure users follow proper workflows.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support onboarding and training of internal and external stakeholders in document control tools and processes.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Contribute to the setup and continuous improvement of digital filing structures, workflows, and metadata standards.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Lead continuous improvements to the digital filing structure, metadata rules, workflows, approval routes, and audit trails.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Project Coordination&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support Design &amp;amp; Delivery teams in issuing, tracking, and updating project documents and design deliverables.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Coordinate with consultants, contractors, and vendors to ensure timely submission and approval of design packages.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Prepare and maintain project documentation logs, registers, and reports for management and audits.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ensure alignment between design, construction, and operations documentation during project handover.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support project handover activities, ensuring alignment between design, construction, commissioning, and operations documentation (O&amp;amp;M manuals, test records, as-builts, asset data).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Quality &amp;amp; Compliance&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Monitor compliance with documentation standards and report on inconsistencies or non-conformities.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support internal and external audits by ensuring documentation is complete, accurate, and accessible.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Work closely with the Quality and HSE teams to integrate document control with broader project governance processes.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;u&gt;Requirements&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Bachelor’s degree or equivalent experience in Engineering, Project Management, or Administration.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;3–5 years of experience in document control or project administration, ideally in data center, construction, or infrastructure projects.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong knowledge of document management s

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Location&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;:&lt;/strong&gt; Sines or Remote&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h4&gt;About the job:&lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The &lt;strong&gt;Electrical Engineer (LV &amp;amp; MV)&lt;/strong&gt; supports the design, implementation, and operation of electrical systems that power our large-scale data centers. Reporting to the &lt;strong&gt;Senior Electrical Engineer&lt;/strong&gt;, this role is critical in ensuring electrical safety, reliability, and efficiency throughout the project lifecycle - from concept and design to commissioning and operation.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This function works closely with design consultants, contractors, and internal teams to deliver best-in-class electrical systems across Low Voltage (LV) and Medium Voltage (MV) networks (non-proficient High Voltage support may also be required to support the team).&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Cross functional activities are required in three main domains: “Datacenter Core Systems”, “Buildings” and “Substations”.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h4&gt;Responsibilities:&lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Design &amp;amp; Engineering&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul type=&quot;disc&quot;&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support the design, review, and validation of electrical systems for data centers, covering LV,MV and HV distribution networks (proficient in LV and MV)..&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Participate in the development of single-line diagrams (SLDs), cable routing, and protection schemes.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborate with design consultants and vendors to ensure technical specifications meet project and operational requirements.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Assist in defining design standards, technical specifications, and best practices for scalability and energy efficiency.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Project Execution&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Provide technical input and supervision during procurement, installation, and commissioning phases.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Review contractor designs, material submittals, and method statements for compliance with design intent and regulations.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Conduct site inspections and testing (FAT, SAT, and commissioning).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support troubleshooting and resolution of electrical issues during construction and operation.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Operations &amp;amp; Maintenance Support&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Assist in the transition from construction to operations, including documentation and training handovers.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Contribute to the development of maintenance procedures and electrical safety protocols.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Participate in root-cause analyses for electrical incidents or performance issues.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ensure all work complies with IEC standards, local regulations, and company safety policies.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Cross-functional Collaboration&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Work closely with mechanical, civil, and controls engineering teams to ensure systems integration and performance optimization.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support sustainability initiatives, including power usage effectiveness (PUE) optimization and renewable integration.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Liaise with utility providers and grid operators as needed for MV connections and upgrades.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h4&gt;Preferred Qualifications &amp;amp; Skills:&lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Degree in &lt;strong&gt;Electrical Engineering&lt;/strong&gt; or related field.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;3–6 years&lt;/strong&gt; of relevant experience in electrical design, construction, or maintenance, ideally in &lt;strong&gt;data centers&lt;/strong&gt;, &lt;strong&gt;industrial&lt;/strong&gt;, or &lt;strong&gt;energy infrastructure&lt;/strong&gt; environments.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Solid knowledge of &lt;strong&gt;LV &amp;amp; MV distribution systems&lt;/strong&gt;, switchgear, transformers, and

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Location:&lt;/strong&gt; Lisbon&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About the job:&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This function plays a key role in strengthening our Finance &amp;amp; Accounting function as we expand operations across Portugal. Reporting to the &lt;strong&gt;Accounting Manager&lt;/strong&gt;, you’ll be responsible for ensuring accurate financial records, timely reporting, and full compliance with accounting standards and tax regulations.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Key Responsibilities&lt;/strong&gt;:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Financial Accounting &amp;amp; Reporting&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Manage day-to-day accounting operations, including journal entries, reconciliations, and month-end closing.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Prepare monthly, quarterly and annual statutory financial statements and management reports in compliance with IFRS (International Financial Reporting Standards).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support the Accounting Manager in group consolidation activities and audit coordination.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintain the integrity of the general ledger and ensure accurate cost allocation across projects and entities.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Tax &amp;amp; Compliance&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ensure compliance with local tax obligations, including VAT, withholding tax, and corporate income tax.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Liaise with external advisors and auditors to manage statutory filings and audit requirements.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support intercompany accounting, transfer pricing documentation, and tax reporting for cross-border operations.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Process Improvement &amp;amp; Systems&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Contribute to the rollout and optimization of accounting systems (ERP, expense management, automation tools).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Streamline processes and controls to ensure scalability as the company expands into new markets.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop and maintain accounting policies and procedures that align with group standards.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead and improve internal control and financial reporting processes.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Business Partnering&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Work closely with FP&amp;amp;A, Treasury, and Project teams to provide reliable financial data and insights.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support project-level accounting for infrastructure investments, including CAPEX tracking and cost control.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Translate accounting outputs into actionable information for management decision-making.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;u&gt;Requirements&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Degree in Accounting, Finance, or a related field.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Certified Accountant (CC)&lt;/strong&gt; in Portugal, or in the process of certification.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;5–8 years&lt;/strong&gt; of experience in accounting, preferably in similar role, audit, infrastructure, or multinational environments.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong knowledge of &lt;strong&gt;Portuguese GAAP&lt;/strong&gt;; familiarity with &lt;strong&gt;IFRS&lt;/strong&gt; is a plus.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Advanced proficiency in Excel and experience with ERP systems (SAP, or similar).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to build strong relationships across teams and earn trust through professionalism and reliability.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Fluency in &lt;strong&gt;Portuguese and English&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience in capital-intensive or project-based industries (e.g., energy, construction, real estate, or data centers) is a plus.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Previous involvement in process automation or system implementations.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A proactive mindset with the ability to balance detail orientation and speed.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&g

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Location&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;:&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;Lisbon (with regular travel to Sines)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h4&gt;About the job:&lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;p data-start=&quot;193&quot; data-end=&quot;645&quot;&gt;As a&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong data-start=&quot;198&quot; data-end=&quot;234&quot;&gt;Project Controls Senior Engineer&lt;/strong&gt;, you will be a key member in ensuring precision and control in one of Europe’s most ambitious infrastructure projects. At Start Campus, we are not just building data centers; we are constructing Europe’s most sustainable data center. You will be responsible for managing the commercial and scheduling aspects of the projects, ensuring that all work stays on track in terms of time, budget, and execution.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p data-start=&quot;647&quot; data-end=&quot;1024&quot;&gt;You will report directly to the Head of Design &amp;amp; Delivery and collaborate closely with teams to ensure all tasks related to construction and infrastructure are on schedule. Your role will involve preparing capital and lifecycle estimates, reviewing cost planning, monitoring schedule submissions, and identifying risks to ensure that the projects meet performance expectations.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h4&gt;Responsibilities:&lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;ul type=&quot;disc&quot;&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;span lang=&quot;EN-GB&quot; data-olk-copy-source=&quot;MessageBody&quot;&gt;Preparing capital and lifecycle estimates&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;span lang=&quot;EN-GB&quot;&gt;Provide input on tendering procedures and results&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;span lang=&quot;EN-GB&quot;&gt;Review PMO cost planning&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;span lang=&quot;EN-GB&quot;&gt;Review of contractor and vendor pay applications, as recommended by the PMO&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;span lang=&quot;EN-GB&quot;&gt;Monitor and report on P6 schedule submissions, Level 3 to level 5, from the PMO and contractors.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;span lang=&quot;EN-GB&quot;&gt;Understand critical path and key risks.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;span lang=&quot;EN-GB&quot;&gt;Provides performance updates / reports views for identification of variances and corrective action&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;span lang=&quot;EN-GB&quot;&gt;Regular reporting on all the above&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h4&gt;Preferred Qualifications &amp;amp; Skills:&lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;ul type=&quot;disc&quot;&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;span lang=&quot;EN-GB&quot; data-olk-copy-source=&quot;MessageBody&quot;&gt;Estimating/quantity surveying qualification 5-8 years’ experience&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;span lang=&quot;EN-GB&quot;&gt;Be proficient in Primavera P6 scheduling tools with project experience&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;span lang=&quot;EN-GB&quot;&gt;Good organisational skills and ability to produce accurate work to deadlines&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;span lang=&quot;EN-GB&quot;&gt;Data Center or complex projects experience in similar roles.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;span lang=&quot;EN-US&quot;&gt;Ability to work effectively as part of a team while prioritizing work efficiently.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;span lang=&quot;EN-US&quot;&gt;Ability to learn quickly and adapt to new processes, procedures, and equipment.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;span lang=&quot;EN-US&quot;&gt;Ability to prioritize in a complex, fast-paced environment.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;span lang=&quot;EN-US&quot;&gt;Effective written and verbal communication skills.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;span lang=&quot;EN-US&quot;&gt;High proficiency of Portuguese and English (being the day-to-day preferred language)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span lang=&quot;EN-GB&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
